The paper deals with the problem of topology and parameter estimation in distribution grids, which involves control and optimization efforts in the grid. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper proposes two algorithms for exact topology and impedance estimation, which involves statistical analysis and computational complexity, indicating that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the sample complexity of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with the operation of distribution grids in the smart-grid era, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ETM).
